## Verify pipeline — tier ladder

| Tier | Moment | Command | Cost |
|---|---|---|---|
| L0 | every edit / agent task | `pnpm gate -- <paths>` | ~15–45s warm |
| L1 | every `git commit` | lint-staged (auto) | changed files |
| L2 | before push | `pnpm gate:push` | ~2–5 min warm |
| L3 | pre-merge / route risk | `pnpm gate:merge` | ~5–10 min |
| L4 | CI gate | `pnpm verify` (sequential, includes coverage) | CI |
| L5 | operational | `pnpm test:e2e:ci` | runtime |

**Use the lowest sufficient tier.** Never run `pnpm knip` after individual task completions.

### What each gate validates

- **`pnpm gate:push`** → lint:full + typecheck:full + knip + format:check + behavior tests
- **`pnpm lint:full`** / **`pnpm lint`** → ESLint + governance scripts (not an edit-loop command)
- **`pnpm typecheck`** → main app type graph (L0)
- **`pnpm gate:merge`** → `gate:push` + `next build`
- **`pnpm verify:artifact`** → `next build` — RSC boundaries, bundle shape, route graph, server/client partitioning, metadata, typed routes
- **`pnpm verify`** → sequential CI chain with coverage thresholds

### CI is sequential — do not parallelize it

`&&` chains: deterministic · fail-fast · single failure identity · coverage included as governance gate.

### Caches (`.artifacts/` — gitignored, acceleration only)

| Tool | Cache |
|---|---|
| ESLint | `.artifacts/.eslintcache` |
| Prettier | `.artifacts/.prettiercache` |
| TS main | `.artifacts/.tsbuildinfo/main` |
| TS test | `.artifacts/.tsbuildinfo/test` |
| TS scripts | `.artifacts/.tsbuildinfo/scripts` |

Phantom TS errors after rebase → nuke: `Remove-Item -Recurse -Force .artifacts/.tsbuildinfo -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue`

### lint-staged (pre-commit, `.lintstagedrc.json`)

- `*.{ts,tsx,mjs}` → ESLint `--fix` then Prettier
- `*.{css,json}` → Prettier only

Do **not** add whole-repo tools (knip, agent-contract, design-contract, drizzle-journal) to lint-staged — they need the full file graph.
